Snippet of ATC audio from the incident involving Alaska 1282 from Portland, OR (PDX) to Ontario, CA (ONT).  See below for my synopsis: Alaska Airlines CEO Ben Minicucci announced Friday evening that the airlineâ€™s fleet of Boeing 737-9 MAXs would be grounded pending emergency maintenance inspections.  This comes on the heels of an incident onboard Alaska Airlines Flight 1282 from Portland, OR (PDX) to Ontario, CA (ONT), where a plugged/inoperative door separated from the fuselage.  This caused a massive hole to open in an otherwise normal window NON-EXIT ROW seat.  The seat in question, 26A, remained inside the aircraft and was unoccupied at the time.  A small child was seated in the adjacent seat and a portion of his clothing was ripped from his body and sucked out of the aircraft.  No other injuries were reported among the 172 passengers and 6 crew members.  The jet was passing through 16,300-ft when the explosive decompression occurred.  This caused oxygen masks to fall and be worn by all onboard until the jet was below a breathable/comfortable altitude of 10,000-ft.  The aircraft diverted back to Portland, OR.  The aircraft, N701AL, was delivered new to the airline in October and began flying passengers December 7, 2023.  The new aircraft had experienced two separate pressurization issues on flights the day prior to the incident on January 4.  Both occurrences led Alaska Airlines to remove the aircraft from flying routes over water to Hawaii.  The airline elected to leave the jet in service since both occurrences happened on the ground and at the time did not indicate an immediate danger to flight operations.  The plugged door is found on all Boeing 737-9 MAX aircraft in the United States.  The door appears to be a normal window seat since it is not an active door and cannot be opened without major modification to the aircraft.  It is only used when airlines order the aircraft with the extra door configured for high capacity operations, unlike Alaskaâ€™s with 178 seats.  LionAir Indonesia has 221 all economy seats on the same type of aircraft, leading them to use the extra door.   #airline #planecrash #alaskaairlines #accident #aviation #alaska1282 #alaska #alaskaair

CNN's Elizabeth Wagmeister interviews Gypsy Rose Blanchard, who was released from prison after serving eight years over a plot to kill her abusive mother, Dee Dee Blanchard. She pleaded guilty to second-degree murder in 2016 and admitted that she convinced her then-boyfriend to stab her mother to death. Blanchard was a victim of Munchausen syndrome by proxy, a rare disorder in which a caregiver feigns or exaggerates illness in someone to elicit attention or sympathy. She had spent her childhood and early adulthood believing she suffered from a host of serious ailments, including leukemia, muscular dystrophy and asthma. After the abuse she experienced at the hands of her mother came to light, Blanchard was sentenced to 10 years in prison and released two years early on December 28th. According to the Missouri Department of Corrections, she is expected to remain under parole supervision until June 2025. #cnn

At lastâ€¦ multiple episodes of The Beatles Cartoon have been found in their original crisp high quality for the first time ever. Since bootleg VHS and DVDs have been around, The Beatles Cartoon always relied on pretty much the same recycled recordings from when MTV aired re-runs of the show in 1986-87, but unfortunately with even the best sources the quality was always fuzzy, oversaturated and lacked a lot of detail. Here is a direct comparison of the newly scanned original 1967 16mm print on top, and the previously highest quality version we ever had on the bottom. Somewhere, somehow, full broadcast episodes and sing-alongs have been discovered and scanned. They were released on a bootleg DVD in 2020 but made pretty much no noise until yesterday that The Beatles Videos on Youtube had brought to my attention that they found these scans and are de-interlacing them! And now for the first time ever digitally, we are able to see the true beauty and detail of the original show. For those who donâ€™t know, much of the staff who worked on this cartoon series ended up shifting over to Yellow Submarine, and this cartoon was pretty much warmup for what that movie would become. This episode is Penny Lane, it was aired in 1967 as part of the Season 3 premire of the series, alongside my favorite episode Strawberry Fields.  This is something I have genuinely been waiting my entire life to see. Since before I could even read and write I can remember taking out the DVD of the fragile bootleg my dad got us and putting it right in the DVD player and watching them on repeat all day. Iâ€™ve been collecting the best versions of the series my whole life and to randomly be blessed with a bunch of full original quality scans of the series for the first time ever is just absolutely groundbreaking to me. Genuinely such an amazing way to send off the great year that 2023 was for Beatles fans, and a great gift to my childhood ğŸ¥¹â¤ï¸ I will be sharing some more info on how theyâ€™re going to be released very soonâ€¦ if you would like to view the raw scans you can find them via The Beatles Videos on youtube! I plan on remastering the audio myself, since whoever released these scans attempted to remaster it themselves but did a sloppy job unfortunately, where the songs can be out of sync and the sound effects are not correct (This is actually MY remastered audio in this clip!). My goal is to organize and share the series in a way that anyone can easily watch it in the best quality and sound! patience everyone! great stuff is coming, who knew we were ever going to get these! it really is something i never thought iâ€™d see ğŸ¥² LAST DAY OF 2023! Their union was marked by a genuine connection and shared interests, notably in animal rights and vegetarianism. Lindaâ€™s warmth and artistic talent complemented Paulâ€™s creative pursuits, and they collaborated musically as well.
